name: src/adt/RedBlackTree.js
RedBlackTree
description: A RedBlackTree with key-only nodes.

name: constructor
description: Constructs a new empty red-black tree.

params.name: compare
params.description: The comparison function for node keys.

name: isEmpty
description: Tells whether the tree is empty.

name: add
description: Adds a key to the tree.

name: _search
description: Search for the input key in the tree. Returns the first node whose key equals the input key. If no such node exists, returns null.

name: get
description: Search for the input key in the tree. Returns the first node key found in this way (with {@link RedBlackTree#_search}. If no such key exists in the tree, returns null.

name: has
description: Returns true if and only if the tree contains the input key.

name: _delete
description: Deletes the input node from the tree.

name: remove
description: Search for the first node of the tree whose key equals the input key (with {@link RedBlackTree#_search}), then delete that node (with {@link RedBlackTree#_delete}). If such a node is found and deleted then return true. Return false otherwise.

unknown.tagValue: {Boolean} - Whether the key existed in the tree before removal.

return.description: Whether the key existed in the tree before removal.

name: range
description:
Returns an in order iterator over the keys of the tree that lie in the
interval [left, right[.

params.name: left
params.description: The left bound of the interval.

params.name: right
params.description: The right bound of the interval.

name: items
description: Returns an in order iterator over the keys of the tree.

name: [Symbol.iterator]
description: Same as {@link RedBlackTree#items}.

name: from
description: Constructs a red-black tree from an input iterable.

name: src/deletion/delete_case1.js
delete_case1
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b

name: src/deletion/delete_case2.js
delete_case2
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root

name: src/deletion/delete_case3.js
delete_case3
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black

name: src/deletion/delete_case4.js
delete_case4
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black
  - n's parent and n's sibling's children cannot all be black

name: src/deletion/delete_case5.js
delete_case5
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black
  - at least one of n's sibling's children is red

name: src/deletion/delete_case6.js
delete_case6
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is black
  - all root-leaf paths going through n have a black height of b - 1
  - all other root-leaf paths have a black height of b
  - n is not the root
  - n's sibling is black
  - if n is a left child, the right child of n's sibling is red
  - if n is a right child, the left child of n's sibling is red

name: src/deletion/delete_one_child.js
delete_one_child
description: Delete a node n that has at most a single non-leaf child. Precondition: - n has at most one non-leaf child. - if n has a non-leaf child, then it is its left child.

src/insertion/insert.js
insert
description: Walks the tree rooted at A down the only path that satisfies the following property: if at a node C we make a left (resp. right), then B < C (resp. B >= C). Once we hit the end of the path, we can add node B at this position. By the property of the path, the tree rooted at A is still a binary search tree. For our red-black tree, all that is left to do is fix the red-black tree properties in case they have been violated by this insertion. This is fixed by {@link insert_case1}.

unknown.tagValue: {Node} B - The node that has been inserted.

return.description: B - The node that has been inserted.

name: src/insertion/insert_case1.js
insert_case1
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.

name: src/insertion/insert_case2.js
insert_case2
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n is not the root of the tree.

name: src/insertion/insert_case3.js
insert_case3
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.

name: src/insertion/insert_case4.js
insert_case4
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.
  - n's uncle is black.

Here we fix the input subtree to pass the preconditions of {@link insert_case5}.

name: src/insertion/insert_case5.js
insert_case5
description:
Preconditions:
  - n is red.
  - n is not the root of the tree.
  - n's parent is red.
  - n's uncle is black.
  - the path from n to its grandparent makes a left-left or right-right.

name: src/rotate/rotate_left.js
rotate_left
description:
Rotate tree left. (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_rotation)
/!\ This swaps the references to A and B.

        A                B
       / \              / \
      a   B     ->     A   c
         / \          / \
        b   c        a   b

name: src/rotate/rotate_right.js
rotate_right
description:
Rotate tree right. (see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tree_rotation)
/!\ This swaps the references to A and B.

        B                A
       / \              / \
      A   c     ->     a   B
     / \                  / \
    a   b                b   c

name: ./doc/manual/installation.md
content:
# Installation
Can be managed using
[jspm](http://jspm.io)
or [npm](https://github.com/npm/npm).

### jspm
```terminal
jspm install npm:@aureooms/js-red-black-tree
```

### npm
```terminal
npm install @aureooms/js-red-black-tree --save
```
